The paper proposes a classifier architecture for online decision making in signal processing, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The proposed method also involves using an ensemble of classifiers, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the algorithm to the bio-chemistry problem of odor classification involves processing sensor data, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of early classification and reject options also suggests a potential application in neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SD).
